    "updated_at": "2014-08-01T01:08:53Z",
    "body": "First, thanks for fixing this so quickly.  \n\nUnfortunately, I'm testing v0.15.1 and it doesn't appear to work (from what I can see the fix is a part of 15.1)\n\nFor my test, package,json is:\n\n```\n{\n  \"name\": \"test9222\",\n  \"version\": \"0.1.0\",\n  \"main\": \"main.js\"\n}\n```\n\nThe main.js is:\n\n```\nvar app = require('app');  \nvar BrowserWindow = require('browser-window');  \nvar mainWindow = null;\n\napp.on('window-all-closed', function() {\n  if (process.platform != 'darwin')\n    app.quit();\n});\n\napp.on('ready', function() {\n  app.commandLine.appendSwitch('remote-debugging-port', '9222');     //  <-------\n  mainWindow = new BrowserWindow({width: 800, height: 600});\n  mainWindow.loadUrl('file://' + __dirname + '/index.html');\n  mainWindow.on('closed', function() {\n    mainWindow = null;\n  });\n});\n```\n\nI test by browsing to: `http://localhost:9222/json`  (where I would expect to see tab information) but there's nothing listening. \n\nSo I inspect the output (I'm on Win7) of:\n\n```\nnetstat -a -n | find \"9222\"\n```\n\nAnd this confirms that nothing is listening on port 9222.\n\nI have fiddled with variations like:\n\n```\n  app.commandLine.appendSwitch('--remote-debugging-port', '9222');   \n```\n"
  },
