    "updated_at": "2014-08-04T01:26:55Z",
    "body": "I have tried exactly that and cannot get it to work.\n\nFirstly I verify that Chrome itself accepts that parameter with:\n\n`...\\chrome.exe\" --remote-debugging-port=9222`\n\nI can then browse to `localhost:9222` and see the windows available for remote debugging.\n\nSo after closing that instance of Chrome, I try running atom.exe itself:\n\n`...\\atom.exe\" --remote-debugging-port=9222`\n\nand our own test app:\n\n`...\\atom.exe\" appfolder --remote-debugging-port=9222`\n\nbut `localhost:9222` displays a \"This webpage is not available\" message.\n\nOn doing a:\n\n`netstat -a -n | find \"9222\"`\n\nit confirms that nothing is listening on that port.\n"
